# =============================================================================
# GIT IGNORE CONFIGURATION - Repository Exclusion Rules
# =============================================================================
# Author: merneo
# Purpose: Defines files and directories that should be excluded from version
#          control, preventing sensitive information, temporary files, and
#          system-specific data from being committed to the repository.
#
# Operational Context:
#   This .gitignore file ensures that sensitive credentials, API keys, temporary
#   files, and user-specific configurations are not accidentally committed to
#   the public GitHub repository. Critical for maintaining security and keeping
#   the repository clean and portable.
#
# Security Focus:
#   - API keys and authentication tokens (never commit these)
#   - User credentials and passwords (sensitive data)
#   - Environment-specific configurations (may contain secrets)
#   - Shell configuration files (may contain API keys or tokens)
#
# File Types Excluded:
#   - Log files (*.log) - Temporary, can be regenerated
#   - Editor swap files (*.swp, *.swo) - Temporary editor state
#   - IDE configuration (.vscode/, .idea/) - User-specific, not portable
#   - OS-specific files (.DS_Store) - macOS metadata
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# API KEYS & SECRETS - NEVER SHARE!
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude all files containing sensitive authentication information
#
# Security Rationale:
#   - API keys, tokens, and passwords must never be committed to version control
#   - Public repositories are scanned for secrets (GitHub secret scanning)
#   - Exposed credentials can lead to unauthorized access and security breaches
#
# Shell Configuration Files:
#   - .bashrc, .zshrc, .bash_profile: May contain API keys or tokens
#   - .bash_logout, .profile: May contain sensitive environment variables
#   - Note: Shell scripts (*.sh) are NOT ignored (scripts are OK, configs are not)
#
# Environment Files:
#   - .env, .env.local: Common location for API keys and secrets
#   - *.envrc: direnv configuration (may contain secrets)
#   - Pattern: *.env* matches all environment file variants
# =============================================================================
# Shell konfigurační soubory s API klíči
.bashrc
.zshrc
.bash_profile
.bash_logout
.profile
# Pozor: NEBLOKUJEME *.sh - skripty jsou OK, jen konfigurační soubory!

# Environment soubory
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.env
*.envrc

# =============================================================================
# SENSITIVE DATA PATTERNS
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude files matching common secret naming patterns
#
# Pattern Matching:
#   - Case-insensitive matching (covers both uppercase and lowercase)
#   - Wildcard patterns (*) match anywhere in filename
#   - Examples: api_key.txt, SECRET_TOKEN.env, my_password.conf
#
# Covered Patterns:
#   - API keys: *api*key*, *API*KEY*, *api_key*, *API_KEY*
#   - Secrets: *secret*, *SECRET*
#   - Tokens: *token*, *TOKEN*
#   - Passwords: *password*, *PASSWORD*
#   - Credentials: *credential*, *CREDENTIAL*
#
# Why Pattern Matching:
#   - Catches files with various naming conventions
#   - Prevents accidental commits of renamed secret files
#   - Comprehensive coverage (better safe than sorry)
# =============================================================================
*api*key*
*API*KEY*
*api_key*
*API_KEY*
*secret*
*SECRET*
*token*
*TOKEN*
*password*
*PASSWORD*
*credential*
*CREDENTIAL*

# =============================================================================
# CLI TOOL CONFIGURATION FILES
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude configuration files from CLI tools that may contain API keys
#
# Tools Covered:
#   - GitHub CLI: .config/gh/hosts.yml (may contain tokens)
#   - Google Cloud CLI: .config/gcloud/ (contains authentication)
#   - Cursor IDE: .config/cursor/auth.json (contains API keys)
#   - Claude CLI: .claude.json, .claude/ (may contain API keys)
#   - Gemini CLI: .gemini/ (may contain API keys)
#
# Certificate Files:
#   - *.key: Private key files (never commit)
#   - *.pem, *.p12, *.pfx: Certificate files (may contain private keys)
#   - *.credentials.json: Service account credentials
# =============================================================================
.claude.json
.claude/
.gemini/
.config/gh/hosts.yml
.config/gcloud/
.config/cursor/auth.json
*.credentials.json
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx

# =============================================================================
# AI SERVICE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude configuration files from AI service CLI tools
#
# Services Covered:
#   - OpenAI: openai* (API key configuration)
#   - Anthropic: anthropic* (Claude API keys)
#   - Gemini: gemini* (Google AI API keys)
#   - Claude: claude* (Anthropic API keys)
#
# Why Exclude:
#   - These tools store API keys in configuration files
#   - API keys provide access to paid services (cost risk)
#   - Exposed keys can be used by unauthorized users
# =============================================================================
openai*
anthropic*
gemini*
claude*

# =============================================================================
# SECRETS DIRECTORIES
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude entire directories commonly used for storing secrets
#
# Directory Patterns:
#   - secrets/, .secrets/: Common secret storage locations
#   - credentials/, .credentials/: Credential storage directories
#   - *.secret, *.secrets: Files with secret extensions
#
# Why Exclude Directories:
#   - Comprehensive coverage (excludes all files in these directories)
#   - Prevents accidental commits of entire secret directories
#   - Common convention (developers often use these directory names)
# =============================================================================
secrets/
.secrets/
*.secret
*.secrets
credentials/
.credentials/

# =============================================================================
# TEMPORARY & SYSTEM FILES
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude temporary files, editor state, and system-specific files
#
# Log Files:
#   - *.log: Application log files (temporary, can be regenerated)
#   - May contain sensitive information (user data, paths, etc.)
#
# Editor Swap Files:
#   - *.swp, *.swo: Vim/Neovim swap files (temporary editor state)
#   - *~: Backup files created by some editors
#   - These are temporary and should not be versioned
#
# IDE Configuration:
#   - .vscode/: Visual Studio Code workspace settings (user-specific)
#   - .idea/: IntelliJ IDEA/CLion project settings (user-specific)
#   - These are IDE-specific and not portable across different editors
#
# OS-Specific Files:
#   - .DS_Store: macOS Finder metadata (not relevant for Linux repository)
#   - tmp/: Temporary directory (should never be versioned)
#
# Why Exclude:
#   - Temporary files clutter repository (no value in versioning)
#   - Editor/IDE configs are user-specific (not portable)
#   - System files are OS-specific (not relevant for Linux)
# =============================================================================
*.log
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
tmp/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
